john has m number of vehicle . he has n children he agreed with peter to give x number of remaining 
vehicles after distributing maximum and equal number of vehicles to the children .
how many vehicles will peter get? also if the vehicles count as even then mr.peter is seen more lucky 
m=10
n=2
vehicles_to_distribute=m-(m%n)
peter_vehicles=(m-vehicles_to_distribute)//n
if m%2==0:
    print(f"you are so lucky!")
else:
    print(f"peter will get vehicles")
